				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=12492"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=12485"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	You always spend the PP you generate with Factories and Commerce in ship building.<br />
<br />
The amount is determined by your Military CM.<br />
<br />
The formulae is if I remember correctly:<br />
<br />
30% + 5% x Mil CM<br />
<br />
So, if you have Mil CM of 6 and have a total production of 10 Mil PP you spend 10 Mil x 60% = 6 Mil PP in ship building each turn.<br />
<br />
If you have no ships ordered PP will be stored into the ship investment pool. <br />
<br />
If you have ordered ships and your ship investment pool is filled another 50% will be added to ship building, i.e in the case above 6 Mil + 3 Mil = 9 Mil will be spend into ship building each turn while those 3 Mil will be drawn from ship investment pool until it's empty or ships finished/or canceled. <br />
<br />
Complicated isn't it ;)			   <P align=right></P>
